name: Incline Push Up Depth Jump
instructions: Step:1 Find an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, and place your hands shoulder-width apart on the edge. | Step:2 Step your feet back, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the edge of the surface, bending your elbows and keeping your body aligned. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Jump off the edge of the surface, landing softly with your knees slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and depth jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Astride Jumps (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Jump explosively upwards, extending your legs and arms. | Step:4 While in the air, spread your legs apart and bring your arms out to the sides. | Step:5 Land softly with your feet shoulder-width apart, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Semi Squat Jump (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Jump explosively, extending your hips and knees while swinging your arms for momentum. | Step:4 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next repetition. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump explosively off the ground, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:4 While in mid-air, quickly bring your arms forward for balance. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next repetition. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Forward Jump
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and lower your body into a squat position. | Step:3 Swing your arms back for momentum. | Step:4 Jump forward explosively, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately go into the next jump. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scissor Jumps (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Jump off the ground and simultaneously cross your right leg in front of your left leg. | Step:3 As you land, quickly switch legs, crossing your left leg in front of your right leg. | Step:4 Continue alternating legs and jumping as quickly as possible. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jack Jump (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet together and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Jump up, spreading your feet apart and raising your arms above your head. | Step:3 As you land, quickly jump back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lunge With Jump
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Push off with your right foot and jump into the air, switching the position of your feet mid-air. | Step:4 Land softly with your left foot forward and immediately lower your body into a lunge position. | Step:5 Continue alternating between lunges and jumps for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bodyweight Drop Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump up explosively, extending your hips, knees, and ankles. | Step:4 While in mid-air, quickly bring your feet together. | Step:5 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately drop back into a squat position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Star Jump (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and jump up explosively. | Step:3 As you jump, spread your legs and extend your arms out to the sides, forming a star shape with your body. | Step:4 Land softly on the balls of your feet with your knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Box Jump Down With One Leg Stabilization
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a box or platform with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees and jump onto the box, landing softly with one foot on the box and the other foot hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Stabilize yourself on the box with the foot that is on it, while keeping the other foot off the ground. | Step:4 Hold this position for a few seconds, engaging your calf muscles to maintain balance. | Step:5 Slowly step down with the foot that is on the box, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat the exercise with the other leg.

name: Jump Squat V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Jump explosively, extending your hips and knees fully. | Step:4 Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately lower your body back into a squat position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Backward Jump
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and jump backwards, pushing off with both feet. | Step:3 Land softly on the balls of your feet, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Incline Push Up Depth Jump With Complex
instructions: Step:1 Find an elevated surface, such as a bench or step, and place your hands shoulder-width apart on the edge. | Step:2 Step your feet back, keeping your body in a straight line from head to heels. | Step:3 Lower your chest towards the edge of the surface, bending your elbows and keeping your body aligned. Maintain complex form throughout. | Step:4 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:5 Jump off the edge of the surface, landing softly with your knees slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat the push-up and depth jump for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Single Leg Squat (Pistol) Male
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Lift your right foot off the ground and extend it forward. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body down by bending your left knee and pushing your hips back. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight as you lower yourself down. | Step:5 Lower until your left thigh is parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Side Wrist Pull Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended in front of you. | Step:2 Extend your right arm out to the side, parallel to the ground, with your palm facing down. | Step:3 With your left hand, grab your right hand and gently pull it towards your body, feeling a stretch in your right forearm. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Cable Incline Fly (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Set up a stability ball at an incline angle. | Step:2 Attach the cable handles to the high pulleys of a cable machine. | Step:3 Sit on the stability ball facing away from the machine, with your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:4 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:5 Lean forward slightly, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:6 With a controlled motion, bring your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:7 Continue the motion until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:8 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Squat On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the bosu ball on the ground with the flat side up. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and position yourself on top of the bosu ball. | Step:3 Lower your body down by bending your knees and hips, as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your weight on your heels. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and keep it off the ground throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in your right hand. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and lift your right foot slightly off the ground. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, hinge forward at the hips and lower the dumbbell towards the ground. | Step:4 At the same time, extend your right leg straight behind you, maintaining a slight bend in your left knee. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell until your torso and right leg are parallel to the ground. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Reverse Hyper Extension (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you for stability. | Step:3 Engaging your glutes and hamstrings, lift your legs up towards the ceiling as high as you can. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Back Extension On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it, with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall or other stable surface. | Step:2 Position your hands behind your head or crossed over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Knees Off Ground
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it, with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall for stability. | Step:2 Position your hands behind your head or crossed over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of the smith machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Place one foot behind you on a bench or step, with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Hold onto the smith machine bar for stability. | Step:4 Bend your front knee and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your back straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Dumbbell Biceps Curl V Sit On Bosu Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bosu ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing forward and your arms fully extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl the weights while contracting your biceps. | Step:4 Continue to raise the dumbbells until your biceps are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your biceps. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly begin to lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Single Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left foot and lift your right foot slightly off the ground. | Step:3 Hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and your right leg extended behind you for balance. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body and your left leg slightly bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a resistance band around your ankles. | Step:2 Take a big step forward with your right foot and a smaller step back with your left foot. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body until your right thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your left knee slightly above the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Dumbbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with one foot and position your feet so that your front foot is flat on the ground and your back foot is elevated on a bench or step. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip, keeping your back knee slightly bent and your back heel off the ground. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Hands Behind Head
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it with your hips resting on the ball. | Step:2 Position your feet against a wall or other stable surface for support. | Step:3 Cross your arms behind your head, with your hands touching the back of your head. | Step:4 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your hips. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Arms Extended
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and lie face down on top of it, with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall for stability. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, with your palms facing down. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, keeping your back straight and your neck in line with your spine. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Russian Twists (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Lean back slightly while keeping your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:4 Twist your torso to the right, bringing the cable handle towards your right hip. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then twist your torso to the left, bringing the cable handle towards your left hip. | Step:6 Continue alternating twists for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball One Legged Diagonal Kick Hamstring Curl
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back with your legs extended and your heels resting on top of the stability ball. | Step:2 Place your arms by your sides for stability. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and core muscles to lift your hips off the ground, creating a straight line from your shoulders to your heels. | Step:4 Bend your right knee and bring it towards your chest, keeping your left leg extended and your foot flexed. | Step:5 Kick your right leg diagonally across your body, extending it fully and engaging your hamstrings. | Step:6 Slowly return your right leg to the starting position, maintaining control and stability. | Step:7 Repeat the movement with your left leg, alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Back Extension With Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying face down on the stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your feet firmly planted on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line from your head to your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips and legs stable. | Step:5 Return to the center and repeat the rotation to the other side. | Step:6 Lower your upper body back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and place a resistance band around your ankles. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and rest the top of your foot on a bench or step behind you. | Step:3 Hold onto a support with one hand for balance. | Step:4 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your knee in line with your toes. | Step:5 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Single Leg Calf Raise (On A Dumbbell)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel as high as possible, using your calf muscles. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Dumbbell Burpee
secondary_muscles: quadriceps, hamstrings, calves, shoulders, triceps, core
instructions: Step:1 Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position, placing the dumbbells on the ground in front of you. | Step:3 Kick your feet back into a push-up position, keeping your body in a straight line. | Step:4 Perform a push-up, bending your elbows and lowering your chest towards the ground. | Step:5 Jump your feet back towards your hands, landing in a squat position. | Step:6 Stand up explosively, lifting the dumbbells off the ground and bringing them to your shoulders. | Step:7 Press the dumbbells overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Lower the dumbbells back to your shoulders and repeat the entire sequence for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Single Leg Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Take a large step forward with one leg, keeping your torso upright. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your front knee and hip, while keeping your back leg straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Weighted Hyperextension (On Stability Ball)
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself face down on a stability ball with your hips resting on the ball and your feet against a wall for stability. | Step:2 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lift your upper body off the ball, extending your back until your body forms a straight line. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Balance Cable Incline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a low position and attach the handles. | Step:2 Sit on an incline bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the floor. Perform with balance intensity. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stability Style Band Kneeling One Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point above your head. | Step:2 Kneel down and hold the band with one hand, palm facing down. | Step:3 Extend your arm fully overhead, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:4 Engage your lat muscles and pull the band down towards your side, bringing your elbow towards your ribcage. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly release the tension and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides. Perform with stability intensity.

name: Targeted Style Single Leg Calf Raise (On A Dumbbell)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and balance on the other foot. | Step:3 Slowly raise your heel as high as possible, using your calf muscles. Emphasize targeted control. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Barbell Standing Ab Rollerout
instructions: Step:1 Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell with both hands in front of your thighs. | Step:2 Engage your core and slowly roll the barbell down towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your arms extended. | Step:3 Continue rolling the barbell forward until your body is fully extended and your hands are directly above your head. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly roll the barbell back towards your thighs, maintaining control and keeping your core engaged. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rollerout From Bench
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the floor with a barbell placed on a bench in front of you. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, slowly roll the barbell forward, extending your arms in front of you. | Step:4 Continue rolling the barbell forward until your body is fully extended and your arms are overhead. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly roll the barbell back towards your body, returning to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Controlled Band Straight Back Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your upper legs. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent, hinge at the hips and lower the band towards the ground. Focus on controlled movement. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your hamstrings as you lower the band. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Single Leg Bridge With Outstretched Leg
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Engage your glutes and lift your hips off the ground, forming a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. | Step:4 Hold for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Kneeling Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your feet hip-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold a barbell across your upper back, resting it on your shoulders. | Step:3 Engage your core and glutes, then explosively jump up into the air, extending your hips and knees. | Step:4 As you jump, push through your toes and fully extend your ankles, knees, and hips. | Step:5 Land softly back on the ground, bending your knees to absorb the impact. | Step:6 Immediately go into the next repetition, repeating the jump squat motion.

name: Barbell Jump Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Once you reach the bottom of the squat, explode upwards by jumping off the ground. | Step:4 As you jump, extend your hips, knees, and ankles, pushing through your toes. | Step:5 Land softly back into the squat position and immediately repeat the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Jump Rope
instructions: Step:1 Hold the handles of the jump rope with your hands, palms facing inward. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and knees slightly bent. | Step:3 Swing the rope over your head and jump over it as it comes towards your feet. | Step:4 Land softly on the balls of your feet and repeat the jump as the rope comes around again. | Step:5 Continue jumping for the desired duration or number of repetitions.

name: Archer Pull Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull your shoulder blades down and back. | Step:3 As you pull yourself up, bend one arm and bring your elbow towards your side, while keeping the other arm straight. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar and your bent arm is fully flexed. | Step:5 Lower yourself back down with control, straightening the bent arm and repeating the movement on the other side. | Step:6 Alternate sides with each repetition.

name: Bodyweight Kneeling Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Kneel down on the ground with your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you, shoulder-width apart, fingers pointing forward. | Step:3 Extend your legs straight behind you, balancing on your toes and hands, forming a straight line from head to heels. | Step:4 Bend your elbows and lower your upper body towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your hands to straighten your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hyperextension (On Bench)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the hyperextension bench so that your hips are resting comfortably on the pad and your feet are secured. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head. | Step:3 Slowly lower your upper body towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise your upper body back up until it is in line with your legs. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Push And Pull Bodyweight
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your body in a straight line. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:3 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:4 From the push-up position, pull your chest towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping your body straight. | Step:5 Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Suspended Split Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from a suspension trainer with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward and place the top of your foot in the foot cradle of the suspension trainer. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down into a lunge position, keeping your chest up and your knee in line with your toes. | Step:4 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbows and bringing your chest towards the bar. | Step:4 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Curtsey Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step diagonally behind and across your body with your right foot, crossing it behind your left leg. | Step:3 Bend both knees as if you were curtsying, lowering your body towards the ground. | Step:4 Keep your torso upright and your weight on your front foot. | Step:5 Push through your front foot to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, stepping diagonally behind and across your body with your left foot.

name: Squat To Overhead Reach With Twist
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Lower your body into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you come up from the squat, raise your arms overhead and twist your torso to one side. | Step:4 Return to the starting position and repeat the squat, this time twisting your torso to the opposite side. | Step:5 Continue alternating sides with each squat repetition.

name: Stalder Press
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and your arms extended overhead. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Lower your body down into a squat position while keeping your arms extended overhead. | Step:4 As you squat down, press your arms down towards the ground, engaging your triceps. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the squat, then push through your heels to stand back up while simultaneously raising your arms back overhead. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Potty Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Lower your body down by bending your knees and pushing your hips back as if you were sitting on a chair. | Step:3 Keep your chest up and your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Dip (On Dip-Pull-Up Cage)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the dip bars to a height that allows you to comfortably grip them. | Step:2 Stand between the bars and place your hands on each bar, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Jump up and straighten your arms, supporting your body weight on the bars. | Step:4 Bend your knees and cross your ankles behind you. | Step:5 Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping your chest up and your shoulders down. | Step:6 Continue lowering until your shoulders are below your elbows or until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:7 Push through your palms and extend your elbows to raise your body back up to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Bench Pull-Ups
instructions: Step:1 Position yourself under a bar or a sturdy horizontal surface that is at chest height. | Step:2 Grab the bar or surface with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Pull your chest towards the bar or surface by squeezing your shoulder blades together and bending your elbows. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar or surface. | Step:6 Lower yourself back down to the starting position with control. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Wide Grip Rear Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with a wide overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Split Squats
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Take a step forward with one foot and place it about two feet in front of the other foot. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your knees and hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, and your back knee is hovering just above the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your front heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Wide Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rocky Pull-Up Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Stand in front of a pull-up bar with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Reach up and grab the bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:4 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Leg Pull In Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your legs extended straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Shoulder Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with a shoulder-width grip, palms facing away from you. | Step:2 Hang freely with your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar until your chin is above the bar. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lower Back Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your stomach with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, and slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling your back upwards. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Biceps Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and pull yourself up by bending your elbows, bringing your chest towards the bar. | Step:3 Pause at the top of the movement, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Potty Squat With Support
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable support, such as a chair or wall, for balance. | Step:3 Lower your body down into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: One Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward, keeping it off the ground. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other leg.

name: Squat To Overhead Reach
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Lower your body down into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you come up from the squat, extend your arms overhead, reaching towards the ceiling. | Step:4 Return to the starting position by lowering your arms and bending your knees to squat down again. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverse Leg Curl (On Pull-Up Cable Machine)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the ankle straps are at the lowest setting. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your legs extended and the ankle straps attached to your feet. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles of the bench for stability. | Step:4 Bend your knees and curl your legs towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Self Assisted Inverse Leg Curl (On Floor)
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides. | Step:2 Bend your knees and place your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart. | Step:3 Lift your hips off the ground, engaging your glutes and hamstrings. | Step:4 Slowly curl your legs towards your glutes, keeping your hips lifted. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Lower your hips back down to the ground. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Hyperextension
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the hyperextension bench so that your upper thighs are resting on the pad and your feet are secured. | Step:2 Cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head. | Step:3 Lower your upper body towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise your upper body back up until it is in line with your legs. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rollerout
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the floor and hold a barbell with both hands, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Roll the barbell forward, extending your arms and keeping your core engaged. | Step:3 Continue rolling forward until your body is fully extended and your arms are overhead. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly roll the barbell back towards your knees, maintaining control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Inverse Leg Curl (Bench Support)
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a bench with your hips at the edge and your legs extended straight behind you. | Step:2 Hold onto the bench for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper body still, bend your knees and curl your legs towards your glutes. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly extend your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sissy Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body by bending your knees and leaning back, keeping your torso upright. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as far as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Scapular Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start by hanging from a pull-up bar with your palms facing away from you and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Retract your shoulder blades by pulling them down and back. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, focusing on squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Self Assisted Inverse Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a leg curl machine with your legs extended and your ankles hooked under the padded lever. | Step:2 Place your hands on the side handles of the machine for support. | Step:3 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause as you squeeze your hamstrings. | Step:5 Slowly lower your legs back to the starting position while inhaling. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Pull Up (Neutral Grip)
instructions: Step:1 Hang from a pull-up bar with a neutral grip (palms facing each other) and your arms fully extended. | Step:2 Engage your core and squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:3 Pull your body up towards the bar by bending your elbows and driving your elbows down towards your hips. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position with control. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Grip Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, leading with your chest. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Rear Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang from the bar with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your back muscles and pull your body up towards the bar, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: L-Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Grab the pull-up bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hang with your arms fully extended and your body straight. | Step:3 Engage your lats and biceps to pull your body up towards the bar, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your body back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Self Assisted Inverse Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a mat or bench with your legs extended. | Step:2 Place your hands by your sides or under your glutes for support. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lift your feet off the ground, bringing your thighs towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Slow Leg Pull In Flat Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with your legs extended straight out in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the bench beside your hips for support. | Step:3 Engage your abs and lift your legs off the ground, bringing your knees towards your chest. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your legs back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain slow form throughout.

name: Sissy Squat Isolation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold onto a stable object for balance if needed. | Step:3 Slowly lower your body by bending your knees and leaning back, keeping your torso upright. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as far as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Emphasize isolation control.

name: One Arm Against Wall Compressed
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm straight out in front of you and place your palm against the wall. | Step:3 Engage your core and lean your body forward, keeping your arm straight and your back flat. Maintain compressed form throughout. | Step:4 Slowly push against the wall with your palm, activating your lat muscles. | Step:5 Hold the position for a few seconds, then release and repeat with the other arm.

name: One Leg Squat - Expanded Variation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one leg forward, keeping it off the ground. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair. | Step:4 Keep your chest up and your back straight. | Step:5 Push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat with the other leg. Maintain expanded form throughout.

name: Inverted Style Inverse Leg Curl (On Pull-Up Cable Machine)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the ankle straps are at the lowest setting. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your legs extended and the ankle straps attached to your feet. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles of the bench for stability. | Step:4 Bend your knees and curl your legs towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. Maintain inverted form throughout.

name: Standing Lateral Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly lean your upper body to one side, feeling a stretch in your side and lats. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. | Step:5 Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Push Neck Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit up straight with your shoulders relaxed. | Step:2 Tilt your head to the right, bringing your right ear towards your right shoulder. | Step:3 Place your right hand on the left side of your head and gently apply pressure to increase the stretch. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, tilting your head to the left and applying pressure with your left hand. | Step:6 Repeat the stretch 2-3 times on each side.

name: Roller Seated Single Leg Shoulder Flexor Depresor Retractor
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat surface with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Hold the roller with both hands, palms facing down, and place it on your thighs. | Step:3 Lean back slightly and engage your core muscles. | Step:4 Raise the roller up to shoulder level, keeping your arms straight. | Step:5 Slowly lower the roller back down to your thighs. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Lower Back Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Place your hands on your thighs or on the sides of the chair for support. | Step:3 Slowly lean forward from your hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your lower back and hold for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Slowly return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chair Leg Extended Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the ground. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly, feeling a stretch in your quadriceps. | Step:4 Hold this position for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Exercise Ball Lower Back Stretch (Pyramid)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Slowly walk your feet forward, rolling the ball down your back until your lower back is resting on the ball. | Step:3 Place your hands behind your head or cross them over your chest. | Step:4 Engage your core and slowly lower your upper body towards the ground, allowing your lower back to stretch over the ball. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chest Stretch With Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold the exercise ball with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Slowly bring the exercise ball towards your chest, feeling a stretch in your chest muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Assisted Seated Pectoralis Major Stretch With Stability Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a stability ball with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Slowly lower the stability ball towards your chest, feeling a stretch in your pectoral muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kneeling Lat Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Kneel on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your toes pointing back. | Step:2 Extend your arms overhead and interlace your fingers. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, slowly lean to the right side, feeling a stretch in your left lat muscle. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the stretch on the left side, leaning to the left and feeling a stretch in your right lat muscle. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Iron Cross Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended out to the sides. | Step:2 Raise your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Slowly lower your legs to one side, aiming to touch the floor with your feet. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then return your legs to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the stretch on the other side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Side Lying Floor Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight and your bottom arm extended straight overhead. | Step:2 Bend your top knee and place your foot on the ground in front of your bottom leg. | Step:3 Reach your top arm over your head and grab onto something stable, like a wall or a piece of furniture. | Step:4 Slowly lift your bottom leg off the ground, keeping it straight, until you feel a stretch in your side. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then slowly lower your leg back down. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side.

name: Neck Side Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit up straight with your shoulders relaxed. | Step:2 Tilt your head to one side, bringing your ear towards your shoulder. | Step:3 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds. | Step:4 Repeat on the other side. | Step:5 Perform 2-4 sets on each side.

name: Butterfly Yoga Pose
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the floor with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your knees and bring the soles of your feet together, allowing your knees to fall out to the sides. | Step:3 Hold onto your ankles or feet with your hands. | Step:4 Sit up tall and lengthen your spine. | Step:5 Gently press your knees down towards the floor, feeling a stretch in your inner thighs. | Step:6 Hold this position for a few breaths. | Step:7 To release, slowly bring your knees back up and extend your legs.

name: Exercise Ball Lat Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and extend your arm straight up overhead. | Step:3 Slowly lean to the opposite side, feeling a stretch in your lat muscle. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Rear Deltoid Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your right arm across your chest, placing your left hand on your right elbow. | Step:3 Gently pull your right arm towards your left shoulder, feeling a stretch in your right shoulder. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Standing Single Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your hands on your hips. | Step:2 Shift your weight onto your left leg and lift your right foot off the ground, bending your knee. | Step:3 Slowly curl your right heel towards your glutes, squeezing your hamstring. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your right foot back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs.

name: Exercise Ball Seated Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Slowly roll the ball forward, walking your feet out until your upper back is resting on the ball and your legs are extended straight in front of you. | Step:3 Place your hands on your hips for support. | Step:4 Engage your core and slowly lower your upper body towards the ground, keeping your back straight and your chest lifted. | Step:5 Stop when you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, and hold the position for 20-30 seconds. | Step:6 Slowly return to the starting position by pushing through your heels and using your hamstrings to pull yourself back up. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Seated Triceps Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and extend your arm straight up above your head. | Step:3 Bend your elbow and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arm close to your ear. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm.

name: Spine Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground behind you, fingers pointing towards your body. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly lean back, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Continue leaning back until you feel a stretch in your spine. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Lying Side Lat Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs extended and your head supported by the stability ball. | Step:2 Place your top arm on the ball for stability. | Step:3 Reach your top arm overhead and allow your torso to rotate slightly. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your lat muscles on the side of your body. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Standing Calves Calf Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall or sturdy object, about an arm's length away. | Step:2 Place your hands on the wall or object at shoulder height. | Step:3 Step back with one foot, keeping your heel flat on the ground. | Step:4 Bend your front knee slightly and lean forward, keeping your back leg straight. | Step:5 You should feel a stretch in your calf muscle. | Step:6 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:7 Repeat on the other leg.

name: Dynamic Chest Stretch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out to the sides, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Slowly bring your arms forward, crossing them in front of your body. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your chest muscles. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 10-30 seconds. | Step:6 Return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Circles Knee Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and lift your heels off the ground, balancing on the balls of your feet. | Step:3 Keeping your knees bent, rotate your knees in a circular motion, first clockwise and then counterclockwise. | Step:4 Perform the movement for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Hip Flexor Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and kneel in front of it. | Step:2 Place your right foot on top of the stability ball, with your knee bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your left leg behind you, keeping it straight. | Step:4 Lean forward, pushing your hips towards the stability ball, until you feel a stretch in your right hip flexor. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch sides and repeat.

name: World Greatest Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Start in a lunge position with your right foot forward and your left foot back. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground on either side of your right foot. | Step:3 Lower your left knee to the ground and extend your right leg, keeping your right foot flat on the ground. | Step:4 Rotate your torso to the right, reaching your right arm up towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Hold this position for a few seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:6 Switch sides and repeat the stretch with your left foot forward.

name: Back Pec Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Cross your arms in front of your body, with your right arm over your left arm. | Step:4 Interlock your fingers and rotate your palms away from your body. | Step:5 Slowly raise your arms up and away from your body, feeling a stretch in your back and chest. | Step:6 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:7 Repeat on the opposite side.

name: All Fours Squad Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Start on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight back, keeping your knee bent and your foot flexed. | Step:3 Slowly lower your hips towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your quads. | Step:4 Hold this position for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch on the other side.

name: Rocking Frog Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your knees hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands on the ground in front of you for support. | Step:3 Slowly lean forward, shifting your weight onto your hands and extending your legs behind you. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and engage your glutes as you push your hips back and up towards the ceiling. | Step:5 Hold this position for a few seconds, feeling a stretch in your glutes. | Step:6 Slowly return to the starting position by bending your knees and lowering your hips back down. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Stretched Full Planche Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a push-up position with your hands placed slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Engage your core and lower your body down towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 As you lower yourself, lean your body forward and lift your feet off the ground, balancing on your hands. Perform with stretched intensity. | Step:4 Continue to lower your body until your chest is just above the ground. | Step:5 Push through your hands and extend your arms to lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Maintain a straight line from your head to your heels throughout the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Exercise Ball Seated Triceps Stretch Wide
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and extend your arm straight up above your head. | Step:3 Bend your elbow and lower the dumbbell behind your head, keeping your upper arm close to your ear. Maintain wide form throughout. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm.

name: Chest Stretch With Exercise Ball Partial
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold the exercise ball with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. Focus on partial movement. | Step:3 Slowly bring the exercise ball towards your chest, feeling a stretch in your chest muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Chair Leg Extended Stretch With Modified
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the ground. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly, feeling a stretch in your quadriceps. | Step:4 Hold this position for 20-30 seconds. Focus on modified movement. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Exercise Ball Hip Flexor Stretch Pointed
instructions: Step:1 Place the stability ball on the ground and kneel in front of it. | Step:2 Place your right foot on top of the stability ball, with your knee bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your left leg behind you, keeping it straight. | Step:4 Lean forward, pushing your hips towards the stability ball, until you feel a stretch in your right hip flexor. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch sides and repeat. Emphasize pointed control.

name: Iron Cross Stretch - Deep Variation
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your arms extended out to the sides. | Step:2 Raise your legs up towards the ceiling, keeping them straight. | Step:3 Slowly lower your legs to one side, aiming to touch the floor with your feet. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then return your legs to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the stretch on the other side. Maintain deep form throughout. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: All Fours Squad Stretch - Elevated Variation
instructions: Step:1 Start on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight back, keeping your knee bent and your foot flexed. Maintain elevated form throughout. | Step:3 Slowly lower your hips towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your quads. | Step:4 Hold this position for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch on the other side.

name: Isolation Assisted Seated Pectoralis Major Stretch With Stability Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a stability ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a stability ball with both hands and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Slowly lower the stability ball towards your chest, feeling a stretch in your pectoral muscles. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for a few seconds, then slowly return to the starting position. Emphasize isolation control. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Seated Calf Stretch (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the edge of a chair or bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Extend one leg straight out in front of you, keeping your heel on the ground. | Step:3 Lean forward slightly, feeling a stretch in your calf muscle. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Lying (Side) Quads Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side with your legs straight. | Step:2 Bend your top leg and grab your ankle or foot with your hand. | Step:3 Gently pull your ankle or foot towards your glutes until you feel a stretch in your quads. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Release the stretch and repeat on the other side.

name: Triceps Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit upright with your back straight. | Step:2 Extend one arm overhead, bending it at the elbow. | Step:3 Place your opposite hand on the bent elbow and gently pull it towards your head. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, feeling a gentle stretch in your triceps. | Step:5 Release the stretch and repeat on the other arm.

name: Overhead Triceps Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand or sit upright with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend one arm overhead, bending at the elbow so that your hand reaches towards the opposite shoulder blade. | Step:3 With your other hand, gently pull the elbow of the extended arm towards the opposite side of your head, feeling a stretch in your triceps. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Step forward with your right foot and shift your weight onto your right leg. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, slowly bend forward at the hips, reaching towards your right foot with both hands. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side.

name: Seated Piriformis Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your right knee and place your right foot on the outside of your left knee. | Step:3 Place your left elbow on the outside of your right knee and gently twist your torso to the right. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch sides and repeat.

name: Leg Up Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back with your legs extended. | Step:2 Bend one knee and bring it towards your chest, holding onto your thigh or shin. | Step:3 Straighten your leg as much as possible while keeping it elevated. | Step:4 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:5 Repeat with the other leg.

name: Calf Stretch With Hands Against Wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands against the wall at shoulder height. | Step:3 Step your right foot back, keeping your heel on the ground and your leg straight. | Step:4 Bend your left knee and lean forward, keeping your back leg straight and your heel on the ground. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:6 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Seated Glute Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you. | Step:2 Bend your right knee and cross your right ankle over your left thigh. | Step:3 Place your right hand on the ground behind you for support. | Step:4 With your left hand, gently press down on your right knee to deepen the stretch. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 30 seconds to 1 minute. | Step:6 Switch sides and repeat.

name: Upper Back Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Interlace your fingers and rotate your palms away from your body. | Step:4 Slowly raise your arms overhead, keeping them straight and parallel to each other. | Step:5 As you raise your arms, squeeze your shoulder blades together. | Step:6 Hold the stretch for 15-30 seconds, then release and repeat.

name: Calf Push Stretch With Hands Against Wall
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands against the wall at shoulder height. | Step:3 Step back with one foot, keeping your heel on the ground and your leg straight. | Step:4 Bend your front knee slightly and lean forward, feeling a stretch in your calf. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:6 Switch legs and repeat the stretch.

name: Chest And Front Of Shoulder Stretch
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height. | Step:3 Cross your arms in front of your body, with your right arm on top of your left arm. | Step:4 Interlace your fingers and press your palms together. | Step:5 Gently squeeze your shoulder blades together and push your hands forward, feeling a stretch in your chest and front of your shoulders. | Step:6 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then release. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Calf Push Stretch With Hands Against Wall Elite
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing a wall with your feet hip-width apart. | Step:2 Place your hands against the wall at shoulder height. | Step:3 Step back with one foot, keeping your heel on the ground and your leg straight. | Step:4 Bend your front knee slightly and lean forward, feeling a stretch in your calf. | Step:5 Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds. | Step:6 Switch legs and repeat the stretch. Focus on elite movement.

name: Chest And Front Of Shoulder Stretch Micro
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Extend your arms straight out in front of you at shoulder height. | Step:3 Cross your arms in front of your body, with your right arm on top of your left arm. | Step:4 Interlace your fingers and press your palms together. | Step:5 Gently squeeze your shoulder blades together and push your hands forward, feeling a stretch in your chest and front of your shoulders. | Step:6 (micro variation) Hold the stretch for 20-30 seconds, then release. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Close Grip To Skull Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your head lower than your feet and hold a barbell with a close grip. | Step:2 Lower the barbell towards your forehead by bending your elbows, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then extend your arms to press the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Contralateral Forward Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, keeping your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending both knees until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg. | Step:6 Alternate legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Press Sit-Up
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on a mat with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, resting it on your chest. | Step:3 Engaging your abs, slowly lift your upper body off the ground, curling forward until your torso is at a 45-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your upper body back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Finger Curls
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an underhand grip, resting your forearm on your thigh, palm facing up. | Step:3 Allow the dumbbell to roll down to your fingertips, then curl it back up by flexing your fingers. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand.

name: Band Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your ankles. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and slowly lower your upper body towards the ground. | Step:4 As you lower, push your hips back and allow your knees to bend slightly. | Step:5 Lower the band towards the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your upper body back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Goblet Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell close to your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, lower your body down into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause briefly at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:2 Press the dumbbell upward until your arm is fully extended overhead. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Standing Up Straight Crossovers
instructions: Step:1 Stand in the middle of a cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the handles of the cables with your palms facing down and your arms extended straight out to the sides. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, bring your hands together in front of your body, crossing them over each other. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly return to the starting position, keeping your arms extended. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Full Squat (Back Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to lower your body down. | Step:4 Bend at the knees and hips, pushing your hips back and down as if sitting into a chair. | Step:5 Lower your body until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:6 Keep your knees in line with your toes and your weight in your heels. | Step:7 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Raise And Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:2 Keep your arms straight and raise the barbell in front of you until it reaches shoulder height. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Next, lower the barbell behind your head, keeping your arms straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then raise the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your forearms resting on your thighs, holding a barbell with an underhand grip. | Step:2 Allow the barbell to roll down to your fingertips, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:3 Slowly curl the barbell up towards your forearms by flexing your wrists. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Palm Up
