instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your back straight and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand and place it on top of your thigh, palm facing up. | Step:3 Lift one leg off the ground and extend it in front of you, keeping your knee slightly bent. | Step:4 Raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Cable Standing Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with your arm extended in front of you, parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Keep your elbow slightly bent and your shoulder blades pulled back. | Step:4 Slowly rotate your arm outward, away from your body, while keeping your elbow in the same position. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying External Shoulder Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Lie on your side on a flat bench with your upper arm against your side and your elbow bent 90 degrees. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in your hand with your palm facing down. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm against your side, slowly rotate your forearm upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Straight Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing your torso to lean forward. | Step:3 Continue lowering the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your torso back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, slightly narrower than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Lift
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands and position it at waist height. | Step:3 Engage your core and maintain a straight back throughout the exercise. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, exhale and lift the cable handle up towards your opposite shoulder, rotating your torso. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then inhale and slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Cable Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the cable handle in front of you, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Press one kettlebell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Lower the kettlebell back to shoulder height. | Step:4 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Decline Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting on your chest. | Step:2 Place your feet flat on the ground and keep your back pressed against the bench. | Step:3 Extend your arm and push the dumbbell up towards the ceiling, fully extending your elbow. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Supine Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to a low pulley cable machine and lie face down on a flat bench. | Step:2 Grasp the D-handle with each hand, palms facing down, and extend your arms straight out in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise them out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Hammer Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with your palm facing inward and your elbow bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Press the dumbbell up towards the ceiling, straightening your arm. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Lying Pronation On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on the floor with your face down and your arms extended straight out in front of you, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Rotate your palms so they are facing down towards the floor. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, lift the dumbbells off the floor by contracting your forearms. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your forearms are fully contracted and the dumbbells are at shoulder level. | Step:5 Hold for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Front Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest lifted and your shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Engage your lats and pull the handles down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Bench Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up a barbell on a squat rack at chest height. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the rack, with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:4 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:5 Lift the barbell off the rack and step back, ensuring your feet are still shoulder-width apart. | Step:6 Lower your body down into a squat, keeping your knees in line with your toes. | Step:7 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Upright Shoulder External Rotation
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:3 Rotate your arms externally, bringing the dumbbells up towards your head while keeping your elbows in the same position. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Middle Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach cables to both sides of a cable machine at chest height. | Step:2 Stand in the center of the machine with one foot slightly in front of the other. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms out to the sides. | Step:4 Keep a slight bend in your elbows and maintain a slight forward lean. | Step:5 Engage your chest muscles and bring your arms forward in a sweeping motion. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the center, then slowly return your arms back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Rocking Leg Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, balancing on the balls of your feet. | Step:3 Slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Stiff Leg Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your knees slightly bent. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight, hinge forward at the hips, pushing your glutes back. | Step:4 Lower your torso until it is parallel to the ground, feeling a stretch in your hamstrings. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Assisted Pull-Up
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a pull-up bar or sturdy anchor point. | Step:2 Step onto the band and grip the bar with your palms facing away from you, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hang with your arms fully extended, keeping your core engaged and your shoulders down and back. | Step:4 Pull your body up towards the bar by squeezing your shoulder blades together and driving your elbows down towards your hips. | Step:5 Continue pulling until your chin is above the bar, then slowly lower yourself back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Romanian Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend at the hips, keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent. | Step:4 Lower the barbell towards the ground, keeping it close to your body. | Step:5 Feel the stretch in your hamstrings as you lower the barbell. | Step:6 Once you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, push your hips forward and stand up straight. | Step:7 Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement. | Step:8 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Turkish Get Up (Squat Style)
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back with your legs extended and the kettlebell held in your right hand, arm fully extended above your shoulder. | Step:2 Bend your right knee and place your right foot flat on the ground, keeping your left leg extended. | Step:3 Pressing through your right foot, lift your hips off the ground, coming into a bridge position. | Step:4 Slide your left leg underneath your body, bending your left knee and placing your left foot flat on the ground. | Step:5 Rotate your torso to the left, bringing your left hand to the ground for support. | Step:6 Pressing through your right foot and left hand, lift your torso off the ground, coming into a kneeling position. | Step:7 From the kneeling position, stand up, keeping the kettlebell extended overhead. | Step:8 Reverse the movement to return to the starting position. | Step:9 Repeat the exercise on the other side, starting with the kettlebell in your left hand.

name: Dumbbell Rotation Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight and chest up. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Rotate your arms so that your palms are facing downwards. | Step:5 Slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Reverse Grip Machine Lat Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your knees under the pads and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit upright with your chest out and shoulders back, maintaining a slight arch in your lower back. | Step:4 Pull the handles down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline T-Raise
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing inwards. | Step:2 Lean forward and let your arms hang straight down, perpendicular to the floor. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise them out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, forming a 'T' shape with your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell High Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Place the barbell on your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you begin to squat down, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, extending your hips and knees. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wrist Curl V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your knees bent. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up, and your hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Rest your forearms on your thighs, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:4 Slowly curl your wrists upward, bringing the barbell towards your forearms. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Twisted Flyes
instructions: Step:1 Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and press the dumbbells up to the starting position, directly above your chest, with your arms extended. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbells, rotate your wrists so that your palms face forward at the bottom of the movement. | Step:5 Reverse the motion and bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position, squeezing your chest muscles together at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Single Arm Overhead Carry
instructions: Step:1 Stand tall with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your back straight as you walk forward, maintaining the dumbbell overhead. | Step:4 Continue walking for the desired distance or time. | Step:5 Switch hands and repeat the exercise.

name: Dumbbell Full Can Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides, keeping a slight bend in your elbows, until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Double Windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand. | Step:2 Extend your right arm overhead, keeping your eyes on the kettlebell. | Step:3 Rotate your left foot 45 degrees to the left and your right foot 90 degrees to the right. | Step:4 Bend at the waist to the left, keeping your right arm extended overhead. | Step:5 Lower the kettlebell towards the ground, reaching towards your left foot. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then engage your core and push through your right foot to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Band Horizontal Pallof Press
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at waist height. | Step:2 Stand perpendicular to the anchor point with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the band handle with both hands and step away from the anchor point to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Bring your hands to your chest, keeping your elbows bent and close to your body. | Step:5 Engage your core and maintain a stable stance. | Step:6 Extend your arms straight out in front of you, pushing the band away from your body. | Step:7 Hold the extended position for a few seconds, focusing on maintaining tension in your core. | Step:8 Slowly bring your hands back to your chest, resisting the pull of the band. | Step:9 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Front Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the kettlebell with both hands in front of your chest, close to your body. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips down and back, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Kickbacks On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing inwards and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight back, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Machine Inner Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body, arms extended downwards. | Step:3 Bend at your hips and knees, lowering the dumbbells towards the ground while keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Push through your heels and extend your hips and knees, lifting the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Twisting Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing away from you. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight up over your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbells down towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 As you lower the dumbbells, twist your wrists so that your palms face towards you at the bottom of the movement. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then reverse the movement by pressing the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:7 As you press the dumbbells up, twist your wrists back to the starting position with palms facing away from you. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips and your feet secured. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a pronated grip (palms facing away from you) and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Extend your arms above your chest, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Lower the barbell in an arc motion behind your head, feeling a stretch in your chest and shoulders. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return the barbell to the starting position by reversing the motion. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Waiter Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Keep your upper arms close to your body and your elbows tucked in. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your wrists straight. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Lying Extension Pullover (With Rope Attachment)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to a cable machine and set the pulley at the highest position. | Step:2 Lie down on a bench with your head towards the cable machine. | Step:3 Hold the rope with both hands and extend your arms straight up above your chest. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, slowly lower the rope behind your head while maintaining control. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise the rope back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells to your sides with a slight bend in your elbows, until your arms are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Close Grip Military Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly closer than shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lift the barbell to shoulder height, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Press the barbell overhead, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows at a 45-degree angle. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Close-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a flat bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Using your thighs to help raise the dumbbells, lift the dumbbells one at a time so that you can hold them in front of you at shoulder width. | Step:3 Once at shoulder width, rotate your wrists forward so that the palms of your hands are facing away from you. This will be your starting position. | Step:4 As you breathe in, slowly lower the dumbbells to your side until they are about level with your chest. | Step:5 As you exhale, use your triceps to lift the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Twist Fly
instructions: Step:1 Lie down on a decline bench with your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing each other and your arms extended straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells out to the sides in a wide arc until you feel a stretch in your chest. | Step:4 As you lower the dumbbells, twist your wrists so that your palms face forward at the bottom of the movement. | Step:5 Reverse the motion and bring the dumbbells back up to the starting position, squeezing your chest muscles at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Ez-Bar Close-Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the ez barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled 45 Leg Wide Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the sled machine to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the pad and your feet on the foot platform. | Step:3 Position your feet wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push against the foot platform to extend your legs and straighten your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bend your knees to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Sumo Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:2 Place a barbell on the ground in front of you, centered between your feet. | Step:3 Bend your knees and lower your hips, keeping your back straight and chest up, to grip the barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:4 Engage your core and drive through your heels to lift the barbell off the ground, extending your hips and knees simultaneously. | Step:5 As you lift, keep your chest up and back straight, and push your hips forward to fully engage your glutes. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Bent Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and your arms bent at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Keeping your elbows bent, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Twisting Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a sturdy anchor point at chest height. | Step:2 Stand with your side facing the anchor point and grab the band with one hand. | Step:3 Step away from the anchor point to create tension in the band. | Step:4 Position your feet shoulder-width apart and slightly bend your knees. | Step:5 Bring your hand holding the band across your body, towards the opposite shoulder. | Step:6 While maintaining tension in the band, push your hand forward and away from your body, extending your arm. | Step:7 Slowly return to the starting position and repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:8 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other hand.

name: Dumbbell Lateral To Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Next, raise your arms in front of you until they are parallel to the ground, again keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting it on your thigh. | Step:2 Lean forward and position your upper arm against the inside of your thigh. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm slightly bent and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Seated Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbells in front of you, with your palms facing down, until they are at shoulder level. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell One Arm Jerk
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in one hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. | Step:3 Press the kettlebell overhead in a straight line, fully extending your arm. | Step:4 As you press the kettlebell overhead, simultaneously dip your knees and quickly straighten them to generate momentum. | Step:5 As the kettlebell reaches its highest point, quickly drop underneath it by bending your knees and hips. | Step:6 Catch the kettlebell with a slight bend in your knees and hips, and your arm fully extended overhead. | Step:7 Stand up straight, fully extending your knees and hips, and stabilize the kettlebell overhead. | Step:8 Lower the kettlebell back to the starting position by bending your knees and hips, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pulldown (Pro Lat Bar)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that your thighs are parallel to the ground and your feet are flat on the floor. | Step:2 Grasp the lat bar with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Sit down and lean back slightly, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Pull the bar down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the bar back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Twist (Up-Down)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing the cable machine. | Step:2 Hold the cable handle with both hands in front of your chest, keeping your arms slightly bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and slowly rotate your torso to one side, keeping your hips and legs stable. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the rotation, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat the rotation to the opposite side. | Step:6 Continue alternating sides for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Shoulder Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and backrest of the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles of the machine with an overhand grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push the handles upward and forward until your arms are fully extended, but not locked. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Hammer Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing each other. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down the ball until your head, neck, and upper back are supported on the ball. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbells at shoulder level, elbows bent and pointing out to the sides. | Step:4 Press the dumbbells up and slightly inward, keeping your palms facing each other. | Step:5 Extend your arms fully, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. | Step:6 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Incline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie down on the bench with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest. | Step:6 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Reverse Fly
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Extend your arms straight down in front of you, palms facing each other. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Straight Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to the high pulley of a cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Engage your lats and pull the bar down towards your thighs, keeping your arms straight throughout the movement. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Calf Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Raise your heels off the ground as high as possible, using only your toes. | Step:3 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heels back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Close-Grip Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach the band to a high anchor point, such as a pull-up bar or sturdy beam. | Step:2 Stand facing the anchor point and grab the band with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Step back to create tension in the band, keeping your feet hip-width apart. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your back straight as you pull the band down towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the band back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Plyo Push-Up
instructions: Step:1 Start in a high plank position with your hands on the kettlebells, shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Lower your chest towards the ground, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:3 Push through your hands explosively, lifting your hands off the kettlebells and extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Land softly back on the kettlebells and immediately lower your chest back down for the next repetition. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing forward. | Step:2 Raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, with your elbows bent and palms facing forward. | Step:3 Press one dumbbell up overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:4 Lower the dumbbell back down to shoulder height. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:6 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Front Shoulder Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp the cable handle with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:3 Raise the cable handle in front of you, keeping your arms straight and your palms facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arms are parallel to the floor. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the cable handle back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Palms Down Wrist Curl Over A Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your forearms resting on your thighs, palms facing down. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell towards the ground by flexing your wrists, keeping your forearms stationary. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly raise the barbell back up by extending your wrists. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Decline Wide-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lower the barbell to your chest, keeping your elbows out to the sides. | Step:4 Push the barbell back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band One Arm Overhead Biceps Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place one end of the band under your foot. | Step:2 Hold the other end of the band with your arm fully extended overhead, palm facing forward. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arm stationary, curl your forearm towards your shoulder, squeezing your biceps. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your forearm back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Cable Overhead Curl
instructions: Step:1 Attach a straight bar to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Keep your elbows close to your sides and your upper arms stationary. | Step:5 Exhale and curl the bar down towards your forehead, keeping your upper arms stationary. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your biceps. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the bar to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Deltoid Rear
instructions: Step:1 Lie face down on a flat bench with a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing inwards. | Step:2 Extend your arm straight down towards the floor, keeping it close to your body. | Step:3 Raise your arm up and back, squeezing your shoulder blade towards your spine. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arm back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Kettlebell Seesaw Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in each hand at shoulder height. | Step:2 Press one kettlebell overhead while keeping the other kettlebell at shoulder height. | Step:3 Lower the pressed kettlebell back to shoulder height while simultaneously pressing the other kettlebell overhead. | Step:4 Continue alternating the pressing motion, creating a seesaw-like movement. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Arm Floor Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with one hand, palm facing up, and extend your arm straight up over your chest. | Step:3 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Sled 45 Leg Press (Back Pov)
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the sled machine so that your knees are at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the sled machine with your back against the backrest and your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate. | Step:3 Grip the handles on the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Push the footplate away from your body by extending your legs, keeping your heels on the footplate. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position. | Step:6 Slowly bend your knees and lower the footplate back towards your body, controlling the movement. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand, with your palms facing forward and your arms extended above your chest. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells slowly to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position, fully extending your arms. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Lying One Arm Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your back supported and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight up towards the ceiling, keeping your elbow slightly bent. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell down towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbell back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Cable Decline One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine and grab the handle with one hand. | Step:3 Position yourself with your back against the decline bench and your arm extended straight in front of you. | Step:4 Bend your elbow and lower the handle towards your chest while keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the handle back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Lever Incline Chest Press V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and backrest angle on the leverage machine to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:4 Push the handles forward and away from your body until your arms are fully extended, but without locking your elbows. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly bend your elbows and lower the handles back towards your chest. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Decline Shrug
instructions: Step:1 Set up a decline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your chest and stomach resting against it. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your arms fully extended towards the floor. | Step:4 Keeping your arms straight, raise your shoulders towards your ears as high as possible. | Step:5 Hold the contraction for a moment, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Take a step forward with your right foot, keeping your torso upright. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your right knee until your thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg, alternating legs for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Cross-Over Revers Fly
instructions: Step:1 Attach a D-handle to each low pulley cable and stand in the middle of the cable crossover machine. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with a pronated grip (palms facing down) and take a step forward, positioning your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Bend your knees slightly and lean forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and your abs engaged. | Step:4 With your arms extended out to the sides and slightly bent at the elbows, exhale and squeeze your shoulder blades together as you pull the cables back and upward in a reverse fly motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the peak contraction, then inhale and slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Standing Bradford Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold the barbell in front of your shoulders with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Press the barbell overhead, fully extending your arms. | Step:3 Lower the barbell back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Thruster
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell at shoulder height with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Lower into a squat position by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 As you reach the bottom of the squat, explosively drive through your heels to stand up, simultaneously pressing the barbell overhead. | Step:4 Lower the barbell back to shoulder height as you lower back into the squat position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Supported Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, slowly lower your body down by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Decline Fly
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Stand facing away from the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Hold the handles with your palms facing forward and your arms extended straight out in front of you. | Step:4 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, open your arms out to the sides in a controlled motion. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the fully extended position, then slowly return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Overhead Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell with a wide grip, positioning it overhead with your arms fully extended. | Step:3 Engage your core and lower your body down into a squat position, keeping your chest up and knees tracking over your toes. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Reverse Grip Decline Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie on a decline bench with your feet secured and your head lower than your hips. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a reverse grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Unrack the barbell and lower it slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the barbell back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Front Chest Squat
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell in front of your chest with your hands shoulder-width apart, elbows pointing forward. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Lever Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and foot platform to your desired position. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the foot platform. | Step:3 Grasp the handles or the sides of the seat for stability. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings, and push through your heels to lift the weight up. | Step:5 Keep your back straight and avoid rounding your shoulders. | Step:6 Extend your hips fully at the top of the movement, squeezing your glutes. | Step:7 Lower the weight back down in a controlled manner, keeping tension on your glutes and hamstrings. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Assisted Inverse Leg Curl
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine so that the ankle attachment is at the lowest setting. | Step:2 Lie face down on the bench with your legs straight and the ankle attachment secured to your ankles. | Step:3 Hold onto the handles of the bench for stability. | Step:4 Keeping your upper body stationary, exhale and curl your legs up towards your glutes by flexing your knees. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your hamstrings. | Step:6 Inhale and slowly lower your legs back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Split Squat V. 2
instructions: Step:1 Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Take a large step forward with your right foot, keeping your torso upright. | Step:3 Lower your body by bending your knees and hips until your right thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your right heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with your left leg forward for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Low Bar Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and the barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, slowly lower your body by bending your knees and pushing your hips back. | Step:3 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground or slightly below. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Standing Pulldown (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Attach a rope to the cable machine at the highest setting. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the rope with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:5 Pull the rope down towards your thighs, squeezing your biceps. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then slowly release the rope back up. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, with the band placed just above your knees. | Step:2 Keeping your chest up and core engaged, push your hips back and bend your knees to lower into a squat position. | Step:3 Make sure your knees are tracking over your toes and your weight is in your heels. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Wide Reverse Grip Bench Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a wide reverse grip, slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Lower the barbell slowly towards your chest, keeping your elbows tucked in and your wrists straight. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Fly On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with a dumbbell in one hand and your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Walk your feet forward and roll your body down until your upper back is resting on the exercise ball. | Step:3 Extend your arm with the dumbbell straight up above your chest, palm facing inwards. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell out to the side, keeping a slight bend in your elbow. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then squeeze your chest muscles to bring the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Lever Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height and position yourself on the machine with your back flat against the pad. | Step:2 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:3 Push the handles forward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling during the movement. | Step:4 Pause briefly at the end of the movement, then slowly return to the starting position, inhaling as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Smith Chair Squat
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the height of the smith machine bar to a comfortable position. | Step:2 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:3 Place the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you slowly lower your body by bending your knees and hips. | Step:5 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Alternate Overhead Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder level with your palms facing forward. | Step:2 Press one dumbbell overhead, fully extending your arm. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbell back to shoulder level. | Step:4 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:5 Continue alternating arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Svend Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a weight plate in front of your chest with both hands. | Step:2 Keep your elbows slightly bent and your palms facing each other. | Step:3 Press the weight plate straight out in front of you, fully extending your arms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, then slowly bring the weight plate back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell One Leg Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell across your upper back. | Step:2 Lift one foot off the ground and extend it forward, keeping it parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Bend your standing leg and lower your body down as if sitting back into a chair, keeping your chest up and your back straight. | Step:4 Lower yourself until your thigh is parallel to the ground, then push through your heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch legs and repeat.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Seated Neutral Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a dumbbell in one hand, palm facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearm on your thigh, allowing your wrist to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Keeping your forearm stationary, curl your wrist upward as far as possible. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your wrist back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other hand.

name: Kettlebell Windmill
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in your right hand overhead. | Step:2 Rotate your left foot outwards about 45 degrees and keep your right foot pointing forward. | Step:3 Bend your torso to the left side, keeping your right arm extended overhead and your eyes on the kettlebell. | Step:4 Lower your torso as far as you can while keeping your right arm straight and your left arm extended to the side. | Step:5 Pause for a moment, then return to the starting position by pushing through your right foot and engaging your obliques. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch sides.

name: Dumbbell Iron Cross
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. | Step:2 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the ground, forming a T shape with your body. | Step:3 Pause for a moment, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, hinge at the hips and lower the dumbbells towards the ground, allowing a slight bend in your knees. | Step:3 Lower the dumbbells until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings, then squeeze your glutes and push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:4 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Seated Rear Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench facing the cable machine with your feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Grasp the cable handles with an overhand grip and extend your arms straight in front of you. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, slowly raise them out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Rear Delt Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, palms facing down. | Step:2 Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at the hips, keeping your back straight. | Step:3 Raise the barbell out to the sides, keeping your arms straight, until they are parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Standing Bent Over One Arm Triceps Extension
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in one hand. | Step:2 Bend forward at the waist, keeping your back straight and parallel to the ground. | Step:3 Extend your arm straight back, keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch arms.

name: Dumbbell Incline One Arm Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in one hand, resting on your thigh. | Step:2 Lie back on the bench and position the dumbbell at shoulder level, palm facing forward. | Step:3 Press the dumbbell upward and slightly inward, extending your arm fully. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Smith Seated Shoulder Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat height so that the handles are at shoulder level. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the floor. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and lift them off the supports, extending your arms fully. | Step:4 Lower the handles down to shoulder level, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:5 Press the handles up overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the handles back down to shoulder level. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a barbell with a shoulder-width grip and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, lower the barbell behind your head in a controlled manner until you feel a stretch in your lats. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your head at one end and your feet on the floor. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell with both hands and extend your arms straight above your chest. | Step:3 Keeping a slight bend in your elbows, slowly lower the dumbbell behind your head until you feel a stretch in your chest and shoulders. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then raise the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Arm Bicep Curl On Exercise Ball With Leg Raised
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your back straight. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing up and your arm fully extended. | Step:3 Place your other hand on your hip for stability. | Step:4 Slowly curl the dumbbell towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, squeezing your bicep. | Step:6 Slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:8 Switch arms and repeat the exercise.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Incline Chest Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the incline bench to a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in one hand with an overhand grip, resting it on your shoulder. | Step:4 Push the dumbbell up and away from your body, extending your arm fully. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Lying Supination On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on your back on the floor with your legs extended and your arms by your sides, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Rotate your palms to face up, keeping your elbows close to your sides. | Step:3 Slowly curl the dumbbells towards your shoulders, squeezing your forearms. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Pull Through (With Rope)
instructions: Step:1 Stand facing away from the cable machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:2 Grab the rope attachment with both hands and step forward, creating tension in the cable. | Step:3 Bend at the hips and lower your upper body until it is parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to pull your body back up to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Alternate Press
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an incline bench with a dumbbell in each hand, resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Lean back on the bench and use your thighs to help raise the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing forward. | Step:3 Once at shoulder height, rotate your wrists so that the palms of your hands are facing forward. | Step:4 Push the dumbbells up with your chest and shoulders, extending your arms fully. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, keeping your elbows slightly bent. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, alternating arms.

name: Barbell Speed Squat
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. | Step:2 Hold the barbell across your upper back, resting it on your traps or rear delts. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your hips back and down, as if sitting into a chair. | Step:4 Lower until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Drive through your heels to stand back up, squeezing your glutes at the top. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Sled Calf Press On Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leg press machine so that your knees are slightly bent when your feet are on the sled. | Step:2 Place your feet shoulder-width apart on the sled, with your toes pointing forward. | Step:3 Release the safety handles and push the sled away from you by extending your knees and ankles. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the sled back down by bending your knees and ankles. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Lying Close-Grip Press
instructions: Step:1 Lie flat on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and your back pressed against the bench. | Step:2 Grasp the barbell with a close grip, hands shoulder-width apart, palms facing towards your feet. | Step:3 Lift the barbell off the rack and hold it directly above your chest with your arms fully extended. | Step:4 Slowly lower the barbell towards your chest, keeping your elbows close to your body. | Step:5 Pause for a moment when the barbell touches your chest, then push it back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Rear Lunge
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand. | Step:2 Take a step backward with your right foot, lowering your body into a lunge position. | Step:3 Bend your left knee and lower your body until your left thigh is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then push through your left heel to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat on the other side, stepping back with your left foot.

name: Barbell Standing Back Wrist Curl
instructions: Step:1 Stand up straight with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a barbell with an overhand grip. | Step:2 Rest the barbell on the back of your hands with your palms facing down and your fingers pointing towards your body. | Step:3 Keeping your upper arms stationary, exhale and curl your wrists upwards as far as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated One Leg Calf Raise - Hammer Grip
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench or chair with your feet flat on the ground and a dumbbell resting on your thighs. | Step:2 Place one foot on a raised surface, such as a step or block, with your heel hanging off the edge. | Step:3 Hold the dumbbell with a hammer grip, meaning your palms are facing each other and your fingers are wrapped around the handle. | Step:4 Keeping your core engaged and your back straight, slowly raise your heel as high as possible by pushing through the ball of your foot. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your heel back down to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other leg.

name: Sled One Leg Calf Press On Leg Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the seat of the leg press machine so that your knees are slightly bent when your feet are on the sled. | Step:2 Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and your feet on the sled, shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Place your toes and the balls of your feet on the sled, keeping your heels off. | Step:4 Push the sled forward by extending your ankles, keeping your knees slightly bent. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the sled back down by flexing your ankles. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and engage your core. | Step:3 Raise your arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, keeping a slight bend in your elbows. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower your arms back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Band Straight Back Stiff Leg Deadlift
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and place the band around your upper legs. | Step:2 Hold the band with both hands in front of your thighs, palms facing your body. | Step:3 Keeping your back straight and your knees slightly bent, hinge at the hips and lower the band towards the ground. | Step:4 Feel the stretch in your hamstrings as you lower the band. | Step:5 Engage your glutes and hamstrings to lift your body back up to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Seated Alternate Front Raise
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your back straight and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with your palms facing your body and arms extended down by your sides. | Step:3 Keeping your arms straight, raise one dumbbell in front of you until it is parallel to the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back down to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat with the other arm. | Step:6 Alternate between arms for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Kettlebell Alternating Press On Floor
instructions: Step:1 Start by lying on your back on the floor with your knees bent and feet flat on the ground. | Step:2 Hold a kettlebell in each hand, with your palms facing towards your feet and your arms extended straight up towards the ceiling. | Step:3 Lower one kettlebell down towards your shoulder while keeping the other kettlebell extended straight up. | Step:4 Press the lowered kettlebell back up to the starting position while simultaneously lowering the other kettlebell down towards your shoulder. | Step:5 Continue alternating the press motion with each kettlebell for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Decline Press
instructions: Step:1 Adjust the cable machine to a decline position. | Step:2 Sit on the decline bench facing the cable machine. | Step:3 Grasp the handles with an overhand grip and position them at chest level. | Step:4 Keep your feet flat on the ground and your back firmly against the bench. | Step:5 Exhale and push the handles away from your body, extending your arms fully. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the end of the movement, squeezing your chest muscles. | Step:7 Inhale and slowly return the handles back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell One Arm Lateral Raise
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in one hand with your palm facing your body. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your core engaged throughout the exercise. | Step:3 Raise the dumbbell to the side, keeping your arm straight and your palm facing down. | Step:4 Continue lifting until your arm is parallel to the ground. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the top, then slowly lower the dumbbell back to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, then switch to the other arm.

name: Dumbbell Cuban Press
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height with your palms facing down. | Step:2 Keeping your core engaged and your elbows slightly bent, press the dumbbells up and overhead until your arms are fully extended. | Step:3 Rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing forward. | Step:4 Slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position, rotating your wrists back to the starting position as you do so. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Dumbbell Incline Breeding
instructions: Step:1 Set up an incline bench at a 45-degree angle. | Step:2 Sit on the bench with your back against the pad and feet flat on the ground. | Step:3 Hold a dumbbell in each hand with an overhand grip, palms facing forward. | Step:4 Start with your arms fully extended, perpendicular to the ground. | Step:5 Lower the dumbbells slowly to the sides of your chest, keeping your elbows at a 90-degree angle. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push the dumbbells back up to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Squat (On Knees)
instructions: Step:1 Start by kneeling on the ground with your knees hip-width apart and your toes pointing forward. | Step:2 Place a barbell across your shoulders, gripping it with an overhand grip and your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Engage your core and keep your chest lifted as you slowly lower your body down by bending your knees, keeping your back straight. | Step:4 Continue lowering until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:5 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Palms Up Wrist Curl Over A Bench
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and hold a barbell with an underhand grip, palms facing up. | Step:2 Rest your forearms on the bench, allowing your wrists to hang off the edge. | Step:3 Keeping your forearms stationary, exhale and curl your wrists upwards as far as possible. | Step:4 Hold the contracted position for a brief pause, then inhale and slowly lower the barbell back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable Press On Exercise Ball
instructions: Step:1 Sit on an exercise ball with your feet flat on the ground and your knees at a 90-degree angle. | Step:2 Hold the cable handles at chest height with your palms facing down and your elbows bent. | Step:3 Engage your core and press the cable handles forward until your arms are fully extended. | Step:4 Pause for a moment, then slowly release the tension and bring the cable handles back to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Barbell Seated Good Morning
instructions: Step:1 Sit on a bench with your feet flat on the ground and a barbell resting on your upper back. | Step:2 Keep your back straight and your chest up. | Step:3 Slowly hinge forward at the hips, lowering your torso towards the ground. | Step:4 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:5 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Weighted Cossack Squats (Male)
instructions: Step:1 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and toes pointing slightly outward. | Step:2 Hold a weight in front of your chest with both hands. | Step:3 Shift your weight to one side and lower your body by bending the knee of the side you shifted towards, while keeping the other leg straight. | Step:4 Go as low as you can while maintaining balance and keeping your chest up. | Step:5 Push through the heel of the bent leg to return to the starting position. | Step:6 Repeat on the other side, alternating between legs.

name: Smith Sumo Squat
instructions: Step:1 Set up the smith machine with the barbell at hip height. | Step:2 Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart, toes pointing outwards. | Step:3 Position yourself under the barbell, resting it on your upper back and shoulders. | Step:4 Engage your core and keep your chest up as you lower your body down into a squat position, pushing your hips back and bending your knees. | Step:5 Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground, or as low as you can comfortably go. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom, then push through your heels to return to the starting position. | Step:7 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

name: Cable One Arm Pulldown
instructions: Step:1 Attach a single handle to a high pulley cable machine. | Step:2 Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart. | Step:3 Grasp the handle with an overhand grip and extend your arm fully. | Step:4 Keep your back straight and your core engaged. | Step:5 Pull the handle down towards your side while keeping your elbow close to your body. | Step:6 Pause for a moment at the bottom of the movement, squeezing your lat muscle. | Step:7 Slowly release the handle back to the starting position. | Step:8 Repeat for the desired number of repetitions. | Step:9 Switch sides and repeat the exercise with the other arm.

name: Kettlebell Extended Range One Arm Press On Floor
